<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="46.[151,1436,438,1830]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[197,319,582,607]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,312,582,607]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
A small-sized representative of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bohmann" authorityYear="1952" box="[728,822,582,606]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typus">
<emphasis box="[728,748,582,606]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[763,822,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<typeStatus box="[763,822,583,606]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">typus</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex (referred to “Sp. D” above; see 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="24.[151,249,1851,1874]" captionTargetBox="[333,1169,219,1800]" captionTargetId="figure-139@24.[312,1271,193,1835]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 5. Principal components analysis (PCA) based on nine craniometric variables indicating scatter of individuals on PC1 and PC2 (a) and PC2 and PC3 (b) from six pre-defined taxon-groups of Ethiopian Otomys in relation to existing type specimens of fortior and degeni and new holotypes designated for new species (see Taxonomic Summary). Open squares = O. typus s.s., open triangles = O. fortior; open diamonds = O. yaldeni sp. nov. (= Sp. A); closed squares = O. helleri (= Sp. B); open circles = O. cheesmani sp. nov. (= Sp.C); closed diamonds = O. simiensis sp. nov. (= Sp. D); cross = degeni. Type specimens indicated; normal font indicates existing holotypes; bold font represents newly designated holotypes (see Taxonomic Summary)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280596" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280596/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[180,196,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="26.[151,249,1343,1366]" captionTargetBox="[190,1380,299,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-393@26.[151,1436,279,1318]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 6. Canonical variates analysis (plot of first two canonical variates) of six defined taxon-groups of Ethiopian Otomys based on nine craniometric variables. Position of individuals form “unknown” sample from Oromiya, Jimma (asterisks) predicted a posteriori. Open squares = O. typus s.s. (Mt Guna); Closed squares = O. fortior; open circles = O. helleri (= “Sp. B”); closed circles = O. yaldeni sp. nov. (= “Sp. A”); open triangles = O. cheesmani sp. nov. (= “Sp. C”); closed triangles = O. simiensis sp. nov. (= “Sp. D”)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280598/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[208,236,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="48.[151,249,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,183,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-35@48.[196,1384,177,1946]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 17(a–c). Photographs comparing dorsal, ventral and lateral views of the skulls of holotype of Otomys yaldeni (ZMMU 162594)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280622/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">17</figureCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[292,389,618,642]" captionStart="TABLE 7" captionStartId="29.[151,234,1317,1340]" captionText="TABLE 7. ANOVA of selected cranial variables for 12 proposed taxa of O. typus s.l. Homogeneous groups represent Tukey’s" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Tables 7</tableCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[402,418,618,642]" captionStart="TABLE 9" captionStartId="52.[151,234,1198,1221]" captionText="TABLE 9. Summary statistics for taxa recognised by this study." pageId="46" pageNumber="47">9</tableCitation>
). Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taylor &amp; Lavrenchenko &amp; Carleton &amp; Verheyen &amp; Bennett &amp; Oosthuizen &amp; Maree" authorityYear="2011" box="[559,677,619,643]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yaldeni">
<emphasis box="[559,677,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">O. yaldeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but considerably larger externally (HB mean 
<quantity box="[1196,1288,618,642]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.55" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="155.0">155 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taylor &amp; Lavrenchenko &amp; Carleton &amp; Verheyen &amp; Bennett &amp; Oosthuizen &amp; Maree" authorityYear="2011" box="[1326,1429,619,642]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simiensis">
<emphasis box="[1326,1429,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">simiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cf. 
<quantity box="[186,257,654,678]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6322" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="in" value="143.0">143 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Taylor &amp; Lavrenchenko &amp; Carleton &amp; Verheyen &amp; Bennett &amp; Oosthuizen &amp; Maree" authorityYear="2011" box="[263,345,654,678]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yaldeni">
<emphasis box="[263,345,654,678]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">yaldeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; tail means 
<quantity box="[480,557,654,678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="83.0">83 mm</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[611,689,654,678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.2" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" unit="mm" value="72.0">72 mm</quantity>
respectively); skull having a narrower interorbital region, less pronounced supraorbital ridges, relatively longer nasal bones, and braincase with flatter dorsal profile (
<figureCitation box="[1272,1356,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="48.[151,249,1971,1994]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,183,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-35@48.[196,1384,177,1946]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 17(a–c). Photographs comparing dorsal, ventral and lateral views of the skulls of holotype of Otomys yaldeni (ZMMU 162594)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5280622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5280622/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
); karyotype distinctive (2N=54, NF=56).
</paragraph>
